      "writtenOn": "2017-12-16T07:24:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i am pretty sure this call goes through 1) process cache 2) memcache cache 3) datastore cache and there is a separate cron job (/admin/config/cache/manager) that updates datastore. This increases config change propagation delay by ~10min (process cache and memcache). Caching here is not needed at all, because it is a cron job, so I recommend using config interface directly\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/milo/common/config.go?q\u003dfile:milo+config\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026l\u003d358\u0026rcl\u003de137a647b374734bcd0a6904b23389de95126d12\nand removing the cron job if you have one (I don\u0027t have permissions to the cloud project).\n\nin another CL",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 129
      },
      "revId": "53ab6a41ff4be878b4fde5c4160069f8f71a9bf2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
